    <h1>Where this comes from</h1>

    <p>
      Before Trove Collections became a collection of recommendations, it was a
      family story. This page is where our philosophy comes from — why aviation
      appears throughout the site, and why every recommendation here is expected
      to earn its place.
    </p>

    <p>
      The short version: <em>"If you fly it, you should be able to fix it."</em>
      Grandpa Jim said that to my grandfather — and my grandfather took it
      literally. He's the one in the family who earned the airframe-and-powerplant
      license, the one who stripped and re-covered a Stearman with his own hands.
      The license stopped with him. The standard didn't. Four generations of
      pilots later, it's still how this family decides what to trust — and what
      gets to be on this site.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <p class="lede">
      My family has flown for a hundred years. That isn't an opening flourish — it's
      the literal headline. Lt. Col. James A. Philpott — my great-grandfather, the
      family calls him Grandpa Jim — first soloed an airplane on September 8, 1928.
      He was 16. The brand is timing toward his centennial: September 8, 2028.
    </p>

    <p>
      Four generations later, I'm 20, a Communications major at the University of
      Arizona, headed for the Air Force after I graduate. In between him and me are
      a hundred years of cockpits, a TWA test-pilot job that turned into a 490th
      Bombardment Squadron command, a Continental seniority-list #1 retirement
      handed off mid-flight over the Pacific on a frequency called <em>fingers</em>,
      three sisters flying for major US airlines, a regional-jet pilot cousin who
      flies aerobatic biplanes on weekends, a 1982 TV commercial featuring an acne
      stick, and the teaching Grandpa Jim passed down to my grandfather: <em>if you
      fly it, you should be able to fix it.</em>
    </p>

    <p>
      This is the long version of why every item on the shop has been somewhere.
      We come from people who go places.
    </p>

    <figure class="hero-photo">
      <img src="/images/heritage/family-portrait-4-pilots.jpg" alt="Captain John Philpott with his three pilot daughters" />
      <figcaption>Captain John Philpott with his three pilot daughters (Generation 2 + Generation 3).</figcaption>
